<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include("../partials/head"); %>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include("../partials/header"); %>
    <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Documentation</h1>
            <p>Documentation for the Apartment API</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <h2 id="getall">GETALL</h2>
        <p>
            GETALL returns all documents found in the Apartment database. Use GET-method.
        </p>
        <code>domain/api/getall</code>

        <h2 id="get">GET</h2>
        <p>
            GET returns a single document. An address is used as a parameter to make this call. Use GET-method.
        </p>
        <code>domain/api/get/address</code>

        <h2 id="add">ADD</h2>
        <p>
            ADD adds a document to the database. A document has the following fields.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>type</li>
            <li>address</li>
            <li>area</li>
            <li>room_count</li>
            <li>rent</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Use POST-method.
        </p>
        <code>domain/api/add</code>

        <h2 id="update">UPDATE</h2>
        <p>UPDATE is used to make changes to an existing document. The id of a document is needed to make any changes to it. All of the fields that are used to create a document need to be filled for the update, otherwise, some data will be lost. Use UPDATE-method.</p>
        <code>domain/api/update/id</code>

        <h2 id="delete">DELETE</h2>
        <p>
            DELETE is used to delete a document from the database. The id of a document is needed to delete it. Use DELETE-method.
        </p>
        <code>domain/api/delete/id</code>
    </div>
    <%- include("../partials/footer"); %>
</body>

</html>